# Project Overview

Static, zero-build-step learning platform. Pure HTML/CSS/JS (ES modules). No backend, no npm, no CDN dependencies.

## Constraints

- **Always run a local HTTP server** — ES modules fail on `file://`. Use `python -m http.server 8080` from `site/`.
- **No build step** — edit files and refresh the browser.
- **No external dependencies** — everything works offline after serving locally.
- **Relative paths only** — all HTML links and asset paths must be relative.

## Key paths

- Deliverables: `site/`
- Templates: `site/_template/`
- Design tokens: `site/design-system/tokens.css` (single source for colors, spacing, timing)
- Topic registry: `site/js/topics/registry.js`
- Source notes: `RAG/` (reference only, not deployed)

## Conventions

- One quiz per concept — passing the quiz marks a concept as learned (localStorage)
- Analogy before mechanism — interactive viz teaches without jargon first
- Every failure mode matters — show what breaks without the technique
- Read SOUL.md before writing content; see ERROR.md when debugging runtime issues
